Britain&#8217;s Queen Elizabeth will step down as patron from a number of national organisations in the coming months after she turned 90 in April, Buckingham Palace said in a statement on Tuesday.Her patronage of charities such as the NSPCC, Save the Children and Barnardo&#8217;s, as well as sporting groups like the Lawn Tennis Association and the Rugby Football Union, will be passed onto other members of the royal family in due course.&#8220;Her Majesty will continue to serve as Patron to hundreds of charities and institutions but will now share this work with her family,&#8221; the statement said.Elizabeth is the world&#8217;s longest-reigning living monarch.-Reuters